commitResults.messageTitle: Level 1. Echo Improve the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.
Level 2. Add, List Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3. Mark as Done Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.
commitResults.messageBody: Created a new class called Task to represent tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level 4. ToDos, Events, Deadlines Add support for tracking three types of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Created the following classes which are subclasses of Task
ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it
Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time

commitResults.messageTitle: Duke A-TextUiTesting: Automated Text UI Testing Test using the I/O redirection technique Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
Level 5. Handle Errors Teach the chatbot to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
commitResults.messageBody: Defined a new class DukeException to represent exceptions specific to Duke.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level 6. Delete Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
commitResults.messageBody: Used java collection classes to use ArrayList<Task> to store the tasks.
